{"title_page": "Jer\u00f3nimo Amione", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican-Lebanese association footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Amione|Cevallos}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Jer\u00f3nimo Amione\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Jer\u00f3nimo Arturo Amione Cevallos\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1990|3|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Mexico City]], Mexico\n| height         = 1.75 m\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[Mineros de Zacatecas]]\n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = 2009\u20132010\n| youthclubs1    = [[Atlante UTN Potros Neza|Atlante UTN]]\n| years1         = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1         = [[Atlante F.C.|Atlante]]\n| caps1          = 53\n| goals1         = 8\n| years2         = 2010\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Atlante UTN Potros Neza|Atlante UTN]]\n| caps2          = 1\n| goals2         = 1\n| years3         = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs3         = [[Cruz Azul]]\n| caps3          = 19\n| goals3         = 2\n| years4         = 2014\n| clubs4         = \u2192 [[Cruz Azul Hidalgo]]\n| caps4          = 1\n| goals4         = 0\n| years5         = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs5         = [[Deportivo Toluca|Toluca]]\n| caps5          = 26\n| goals5         = 2\n| years6         = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs6         = [[Puebla F.C.|Puebla]]\n| caps6          = 41\n| goals6         = 2\n| years7         = 2018\n| clubs7         = [[Lobos BUAP|Lobos]]\n| caps7          = 10\n| goals7         = 2\n| years8         = 2018\n| clubs8         = [[Alebrijes de Oaxaca|Oaxaca]]\n| caps8          = 16\n| goals8         = 2\n| years9         = 2019\n| clubs9         = [[FC Lahti]]\n| caps9          = 15\n| goals9         = 4\n| years10        = 2020\u2013\n| clubs10        = [[Mineros de Zacatecas]]\n| caps10         = 0\n| goals10        = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam1  = [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico U23]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 11\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| pcupdate       = 23 October 2019\n| ntupdate       = \n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{MEX}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Pan American Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[2011 Pan American Games|2011 Guadalajara]] | [[Football at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's tournament|Team Competition]]}}\n}}\n'''Jer\u00f3nimo Arturo Amione Cevallos''' ({{lang-ar|\u062c\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0645\u0648 \u0623\u0645\u064a\u0648\u0646\u064a}}; born 31 March 1990) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Mexican club [[Mineros de Zacatecas]].\n\nBorn in Mexico, Amione is Lebanese from his father's side, and Mexican from his mother's side. He represented [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico]] at youth level at the [[Football at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2011 Pan American Games]], winning the tournament. Amione obtained Lebanese citizenship in 2017, however [[FIFA]] didn't consider him eligible for the [[Lebanon national football team|national team]] as he has already represented Mexico competitively prior to becoming Lebanese.\n\n==Club career==\nAmione made his senior debut for [[Atlante F.C.|Atlante]] on 23 April 2010 as a substitute in a match against [[Estudiantes Tecos]], he scored a goal in the 9 minutes he played in a 3\u20132 defeat.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/ficha.php?id_partido=27395 |title=Archived copy |access-date=12 September 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005005405/http://www.mediotiempo.com/ficha.php?id_partido=27395 |archive-date=5 October 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He was runner up in the 2013 [[Copa MX]], where they lost to [[Cruz Azul]]. Later that year, he joined Cruz Azul.\n\nOn 30 December 2018, Amione signed for [[FC Lahti]] in [[Finland]] on a one-year deal with a option to extend it with one further year.<ref>[http://www.fclahti.fi/uutiset/2018/12/30/jeronimo-amione-siirtyy-fc-lahteen Jer\u00f3nimo Amione siirtyy FC Lahteen], fclahti.it, 30 December 2018</ref> He signed for [[Ascenso MX]] side [[Mineros de Zacatecas]] on 23 January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://imagenzac.com.mx/deportes/jeronimo-amione-nuevo-refuerzo-de-mineros-de-zacatecas/|title=Jer\u00f3nimo Amione, nuevo refuerzo de Mineros de Zacatecas - Imagen Zacatecas|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Mexico===\nHe made appearance for [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexican Olympic team]], in which Mexico captured its gold medal in [[Football at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2011 Pan American Games]]. He also appeared in the [[2012 CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualifying Tournament]], however he was not included in the final 18 squad to participate in the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Olympic football tournament]]. Mexico later won its first ever gold medal in their history. Amione scored four goals in 11 appearances for the Olympic team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.femexfut.org.mx/portalv2/secciones.aspx?s=999&ep=171|title=Jeronimo Amione's U-23 National Team Goals}}</ref>\n\n===Lebanon===\nDue to not being further selected into the main squad of [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], speculation emerged that he had opted to join the [[Lebanon national football team|Lebanese national team]]. There rumors were confirmed when he had accepted the offer to play for Lebanon.<ref>http://www.goal.com/es-ar/noticias/jeronimo-amione-acepto-representar-a-la-seleccion-de-libano/1epjoypuj4bo9zgq6xa33stzm</ref><ref>https://deportes.televisa.com/futbol-internacional/jeronimo-amione-campeon-panamericano-a-seleccion-libano/</ref> However, [[FIFA]] subsequently refused the [[Lebanon Football Association|Lebanese FA]]'s request of changing Amione's national team from Mexico to Lebanon on the basis that \"''at the time of his first appearance [...] for Mexico, he did not yet hold the Lebanese nationality''\", a prerequisite necessary for changing national teams.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.docdroid.net/ndtMf0Z/amionefifa.pdf|title=AmioneFIFA.pdf|access-date=2018-11-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Mexico City]], Amione is of [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] descent on his father's side (from the Lebanese town of [[Amioun]]) and of Mexican descent on his mother's side.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/mx/futbol-mexicano/2013/06/22/cruz-azul/245103.html|title=Amione sigue sin firmar contrato con Cruz Azul|last=VAVEL.com|date=2013-06-22|website=VAVEL|language=es-mx|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://atlantefc.mx/noticias/detalle/925|title=DOS ATLANTISTAS DE OR\u00cdGEN|website=atlantefc.mx|language=es-MX|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> He obtained Lebanese citizenship on 14 November 2017.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Honours and achievements ==\n\n===Club===\n'''Atlante'''\n*[[Copa MX|Clausura Copa MX]] runner-up: [[Clausura 2013 Copa MX|2013]]\n\n'''Cruz Azul'''\n*[[CONCACAF Champions League]]: [[2014 CONCACAF Champions League Finals|2013\u201314]]\n\n===International===\n'''Mexico U23'''\n*[[Pan American Games]]: [[Football at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2011]]\n*[[CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualifying Tournament]]: [[2012 CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualifying Championship|2012]]<ref>http://trireport.wordpress.com/2012/04/03/mexico-wins-olympic-qualifying-tournament/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MedioTiempo|jeronimo-amione}}\n* {{Liga MX player|51101/jeronimo-arturo-amione-cevallos}}\n* {{ESPN FC|146556}}\n* {{Soccerway|125017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amione, Jeronimo}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Mexico City]]\n[[Category:Mexican people of Lebanese descent]]\n[[Category:Mexican footballers]]\n[[Category:Lebanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Liga MX players]]\n[[Category:Atlante F.C. footballers]]\n[[Category:Cruz Azul footballers]]\n[[Category:Deportivo Toluca F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Club Puebla players]]\n[[Category:Lobos BUAP footballers]]\n[[Category:Ascenso MX players]]\n[[Category:Lebanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Mexican expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Finland]]\n[[Category:Mexican expatriate sportspeople in Finland]]\n[[Category:Lebanese expatriate sportspeople in Finland]]\n[[Category:Veikkausliiga players]]\n[[Category:FC Lahti players]]\n[[Category:Mexico youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2011 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mexican-Lebanese association footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Amione|Cevallos}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Jer\u00f3nimo Amione\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Jer\u00f3nimo Arturo Amione Cevallos\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1990|3|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Mexico City]], Mexico\n| height         = 1.75 m\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[Mineros de Zacatecas]]\n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = 2009\u20132010\n| youthclubs1    = [[Atlante UTN Potros Neza|Atlante UTN]]\n| years1         = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1         = [[Atlante F.C.|Atlante]]\n| caps1          = 53\n| goals1         = 8\n| years2         = 2010\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Atlante UTN Potros Neza|Atlante UTN]]\n| caps2          = 1\n| goals2         = 1\n| years3         = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs3         = [[Cruz Azul]]\n| caps3          = 19\n| goals3         = 2\n| years4         = 2014\n| clubs4         = \u2192 [[Cruz Azul Hidalgo]]\n| caps4          = 1\n| goals4         = 0\n| years5         = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs5         = [[Deportivo Toluca|Toluca]]\n| caps5   