otball team|Mexico]], speculation emerged that he had opted to join the [[Lebanon national football team|Lebanese national team]]. There rumors were confirmed when he had accepted the offer to play for Lebanon.<ref>http://www.goal.com/es-ar/noticias/jeronimo-amione-acepto-representar-a-la-seleccion-de-libano/1epjoypuj4bo9zgq6xa33stzm</ref><ref>https://deportes.televisa.com/futbol-internacional/jeronimo-amione-campeon-panamericano-a-seleccion-libano/</ref> However, [[FIFA]] subsequently refused the [[Lebanon Football Association|Lebanese FA]]'s request of changing Amione's national team from Mexico to Lebanon on the basis that \"''at the time of his first appearance [...] for Mexico, he did not yet hold the Lebanese nationality''\", a prerequisite necessary for changing national teams.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.docdroid.net/ndtMf0Z/amionefifa.pdf|title=AmioneFIFA.pdf|access-date=2018-11-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Mexico City]], Amione is of [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] descent on his father's side (from the Lebanese town of [[Amioun]]) and of Mexican descent on his mother's side.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vavel.com/mx/futbol-mexicano/2013/06/22/cruz-azul/245103.html|title=Amione sigue sin firmar contrato con Cruz Azul|last=VAVEL.com|date=2013-06-22|website=VAVEL|language=es-mx|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://atlantefc.mx/noticias/detalle/925|title=DOS ATLANTISTAS DE OR\u00cdGEN|website=atlantefc.mx|language=es-MX|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> He obtained Lebanese citizenship on 14 November 2017.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Honours and achievements ==\n\n===Club===\n'''Atlante'''\n*[[Copa MX|Clausura Copa MX]] runner-up: [[Clausura 2013 Copa MX|2013]]\n\n'''Cruz Azul'''\n*[[CONCACAF Champions League]]: [[2014 CONCACAF Champions League Finals|2013\u201314]]\n\n===International===\n'''Mexico U23'''\n*[[Pan American Games]]: [[Football at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2011]]\n*[[CONCA